{"title_page": "Moses Inwang", "text_new": "{{Infobox person\n| name         = Moses Inwang\n| image        = Moses Inwang Sneezemankind.jpg\n| caption      = Inwang on set of Merry Men 2, 2019\n| birth_name   = \n| birth_date   = {{birth date and age|mf=yes|1978|01|31}}\n| birth_place  = [[Surulere, Lagos]], Nigeria\n| alma mater   = [[Obafemi Awolowo University]]\n| occupation   = {{hlist|[[Film director|Director]]|[[screenwriter]]|[[editor]]|[[film producer]]}}\n| years_active = 2000-present\n| known_for    = {{unbulleted list\n  |''[[Merry Men 2]]''\n  |''[[Alter Ego (2017 film)|Alter Ego]]''\n  |''[[Stalker (2016 film)|Stalker]]''\n  |''[[Torn (2013 Nigerian film)|Torn]]''\n    }}\n| awards       = [[Moses Inwang#Awards & nominations|See below]]\n| net_worth    = US$9 million (2020)\n| website      = {{URL|sneezefilms.com/}}\n| signature    = \n}}\n\n'''Moses Inwang'''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.imdb.com/name/nm4657969/|title=Moses Inwang|website=IMDb}}</ref> (born January 31, 1978) is a [[Nigerian]] film director, editor, screenwriter and producer who is best known for making classic films for the [[Nollywood]] mainstream. Inwang came into spotlight and quickly gained critical recognition for directing the psychological thriller ''[[Torn (2013 Nigerian film)|Torn]]'',<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt3460492/|title=Torn|date=2 August 2013|publisher=|via=www.imdb.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://ynaija.com/movie-review-with-torn-moses-iwang-finally-makes-an-impression/|title=Movie review: With 'Torn', Moses Iwang finally makes an impression \u00bb YNaija|date=31 August 2013|publisher=|accessdate=6 January 2019}}</ref> which he produced and released in cinemas nationwide. The movie earned him multiple award nominations and recognition <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.360nobs.com/2013/10/full-list-of-winners-for-giama-2013/|title=Full List of Winners for Golden Icons Academy Movie Awards 2013 Released|date=24 October 2013|publisher=|accessdate=6 January 2019}}</ref> both locally and on the global stage. He then went on to direct and in most cases produce other hit movies like Damage, Last 3 digits, Stalker, Alter Ego, Crazy People, Cold Feet, Unroyal and finally the blockbuster ''[[Merry Men 2]]'' which emerged the 2nd highest grossing movie of year 2019.<ref>https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_highest-grossing_Nigerian_films#cite_note-Top_20_films_14th_20th_February_2020_-_Cinema_Exhibitors_Association_of_Nigeria-7</ref>\n\n\nWith a career spanning over two decades, '''Sneezemankind''' as he is popularly addressed got his first movie credit in 1999 when he co-produced Two Good Men. By 2004 he started his production company, Sneeze Films and kicked off with the movie Save My Soul. In 2008 he directed the movie, Lost Maiden,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sbru0nEcwsc|title=Lost Maiden by Chisom Oz-lee|first=|last=New York Nigeria|publisher=|accessdate=6 January 2019|via=YouTube}}</ref> a film which brought the issue of [[female circumcision]] to the fore, headlining social discussion. He further went on to make Save Our Souls, an educative movie about [[cancer]]. He directed and co-produced Damage in 2011,<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://allafrica.com/stories/201108010242.html|title=Nigeria: Uche Jombo Storms Cinemas With Damage|last=|first=|date=2011-08-01|work=Daily Independent (Lagos)|access-date=2018-04-29|url-access=subscription }}</ref> a film which addressed the issue of [[domestic violence]], which received multiple nominations and carted away with most of the awards.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://blog.irokotv.com/2012/09/17/uche-jombos-damage2012-wins-two-awards/|title=Uche Jombo's Movie Damage(2012) Wins Two Awards|date=17 September 2012|publisher=|accessdate=6 January 2019}}</ref>\n\n\nThe Film ''[[Damage (2012 film)|Damage]]'' earned Inwang nomination for best director at the African Oscars held in [[Florida]], United States,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://maestromedia.blogspot.com/2012/07/2012-nafca-awards-nominees-full-list.html|title=2012 NAFCA Awards Nominees: The Full List|first=|last=Maestromedia|date=7 July 2012|publisher=|accessdate=6 January 2019}}</ref> while the film also won the award for Best Film at the African Oscars Awards.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://letterboxd.com/tajlv/list/the-nollywood-african-film-critics-awards/|title=The Nollywood & African Film Critics' Awards|website=letterboxd.com|accessdate=6 January 2019}}</ref> In 2013, he won the [[City People Entertainment Awards|City People Award]] for Best Director.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gistmania.com/talk/topic,161129.0.html|title=City People Entertainment Awards & full list of winners. Photos Inclusive - Gistmania|date=16 July 2013|website=www.gistmania.com|accessdate=6 January 2019}}</ref>  His 2013 film ''[[Torn (2013 Nigerian film)|Torn]]'' received 9 nominations at the [[GIAMA Awards|GIAMA awards]] in [[Houston|Houston, Texas]] and 6 nominations at the [[Best of Nollywood Awards|Best Of Nollywood Awards]]. <ref>https://www.stelladimokokorkus.com/2013/09/bon-awards-2013-nominees-list.html</ref> In 2014 he went on record as the first Director in Nollywood to receive two nomination as best director at the Nollywood Movies Awards. <ref>https://xplorenollywood.com/nollywood-movie-awards-2014/</ref>\n\n\nHis movie, ''The Last 3 Digits'' was nominated for best comedy at the African Movie Academy Awards AMAA in 2015 and was also chosen amongst the few selected [[Nollywood]] films that were screened to thousands of people at the Nollywood Week Paris.<ref>{{cite web|last=Husseini |first=Shaibu |url=https://guardian.ng/art/nollywoodweek-festival-loud-in-paris/ |title=Nollywoodweek festival\u2026 loud in Paris &#124; The Guardian Nigeria News - Nigeria and World NewsGuardian Arts \u2014 The Guardian Nigeria News \u2013 Nigeria and World News |publisher=Guardian.ng |date=2015-06-03 |accessdate=2020-03-29}}</ref> His movie ''[[Stalker (2016 film)|Stalker]]'', a romantic drama which premiered in Nigeria on 26 February 2016, received 10 nominations and won 3 awards at the 2015 [[Golden Icons Academy Movie Awards]] in the United States. <ref>https://www.bellanaija.com/2013/12/2013-best-of-nollywood-awards-first-photos-full-list-of-winners/</ref> In 2015 ''[[Stalker (2016 film)|Stalker]]'', another film written, produced and directed by Inwang, raked in a 12 nominations at the GIAMA awards Houston and won awards for Best Actor, Best actress and Best Film categories. Still in 2015 Stalker won the award for \u201c Best International Film at the New York film Festival. In 2017 his film ''[[American Driver]]'' from his production company Sneeze Films received a best comedy at The Peoples Film Festival, Harlem New York.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BVXJ1HWDs8H/|title=The People's Film Festival on Instagram: \u201cTPFF 2017 Winner : Best Comedy -American Driver @Regrann from @sneezemankind - Another one! we did it again! TPFF\u2026\u201d|website=Instagram|accessdate=6 January 2019}}</ref> ''American Driver'' was also nominated for \"Comedy of the Year\" at the 2017 [[Best of Nollywood Awards]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bonawards.com/2017/09/06/nominees-for-the-best-of-nollywood-awards-2017/|title=BON Awards &#124; Nominees for the Best of Nollywood Awards, 2017}}</ref>\n\n\nIn 2017, another blockbuster ''[[Alter Ego (2017 film)|Alter Ego]]'' which was produced and directed by Inwang starring [[Omotola Jalade]] was released to a highly-anticipating audience in the Nigerian cinemas and immediately became the most talked about movie of the year. Alter Ego clinched the award for The Most Outstanding Film at the Africa International Film Festival AFRIFF.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://afriff.com/afriff-2017-winners/|title=AFRIFF 2017 WINNERS|publisher=|accessdate=6 January 2019}}</ref> It also won Inwang the Best Director award at the Toronto International Nollywood Film Festival and Best Screenplay award at the Africa Magic Viewers Choice Awards AMVCA with the film getting nine nominations.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pmnewsnigeria.com/2018/09/02/list-of-winners-at-2018-amvca/|title=List Of Winners At 2018 AMVCA - P.M. News|website=www.pmnewsnigeria.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | title=2018 AMVCA: 135 nominees for 27 award categories | website=Latest Nigeria News, Nigerian Newspapers, Politics | date=2018-06-30 | url=https://thenationonlineng.net/2018-amvca-135-nominees-for-27-award-categories/ | language=la | access-date=2020-03-29}}</ref> It was given the best international film award at The Peoples Film Festival NY.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/Bj7XztPnCWJ/|title=The People's Film Festival on Instagram: \u201cThe People's Film Festival 2018 Best International Film \"Alter Ego\" #alterego #bestinternationalfilm #sneezemankind #thepeoplesfilmfestival\u2026\u201d|website=Instagram|accessdate=6 January 2019}}</ref> In 2018, Inwang produced the film Crazy People\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vanguardngr.com/2018/05/ramsey-nouah-nabs-impostor-crazy-people/|title=Ramsey Nouah nabs his impostor in \u2018Crazy People\u2019|date=May 11, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://sodasandpopcorn.com/crazy-people-film-review/|title=Crazy People Film Review: Did It Deliver On It's Promise Of Authenticity?|first=Eddy|last=Mboho|date=June 4, 2018}}</ref> which went on to become one of the top 10 highest-grossing films of that year.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pulse.ng/entertainment/movies/10-highest-grossing-nollywood-movies-in-cinemas-in-2018/fpgtzdf|title=10 highest grossing Nollywood movies in cinemas in 2018|date=January 8, 2019|website=Pulse Nigeria}}</ref> The prolific filmmaker has also release yet another impressive, romantic drama movie titled \"Cold Feet\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://connectnigeria.com/articles/2019/05/moses-inwang-releases-trailer-for-new-movie-cold-feet/|title=Moses Inwang Releases Trailer For New Movie, \"Cold Feet\" \u2022 Connect Nigeria|first=Akwaowo|last=Willie|date=May 2, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bellanaija.com/2019/04/watch-the-trailer-for-moses-inwangs-cold-feet-starring-joselyn-dumas-jim-iyke-beverly-naya-enyinna-nwigwe/|title=WATCH the Trailer for Moses Inwang\u2019s \u2018Cold Feet\u2019 starring Joselyn Dumas, Jim Iyke, Beverly Naya, Enyinna Nwigwe|date=April 28, 2019}}</ref> [[File:Moses Inwang..jpg|thumb]]\n\n\nIn 2019, he was contracted by A.Y and Coperate World Entertainment to direct the sequel to the blockbuster movie, Merry Men, and the sequel, Merry Men 2 went on to emerge the 2nd highest grossing film at the box office at the end of 2019 with a sum of 240 million. <ref>https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_highest-grossing_Nigerian_films</ref>\n \n\n==Education==\nMoses Inwang attended [[Obafemi Awolowo University]].\n\n==Career==\nInwang came into spotlight and quickly gained critical recognition for directing the psychological thriller, ''Torn'' which he produced and released in cinemas nationwide. The movie earned him multiple award nominations and recognition locally and on the global stage. He then went on to direct and in most cases produce other hit movies like Damage, Last 3 digits, Stalker, Alter Ego, Crazy People, Cold Feet, Unroyal and finally the blockbuster ''[[Merry Men 2]]'' which emerged the 2nd highest grossing movie of year 2019.\n\n==Personal life==\nInwang is the surviving male child in a family of six, after loosing his brother at a young age.\n\n==Professional life==\nWith a career spanning over two decades (since 2000), Sneezemankind as popularly addressed by colleagues in the industry got his first movie credit in 1999 when he co-produced Two Good Men. By 2004 he started his production company, Sneeze Films and kicked off with the movie Save My Soul. In 2008 he directed the movie, Lost Maiden, a film which brought the issue of female circumcision to the fore, headlining social discussion. He further went on to make Save Our Souls, an educative movie about cancer. He directed and co-produced Damage in 2011, a film which addressed the issue of domestic violence, which received multiple nominations and carted away with most of the awards.\n\n==Awards & nominations==\n\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n!Year\n!Event\n!Category\n!Film\n!Result\n|-\n|rowspan=2|2012\n|African Oscars Awards, Florida, USA\n|Best Film\n|Damage\n|{{won}}<ref>https://www.vanguardngr.com/2012/07/uche-jombos-damage-anchor-baby-jostle-for-best-film-award/</ref>\n|-\n|African Oscars Awards, Florida, USA\n|Best Director\n|Damage\n|{{nominated}}\n|-\n|rowspan=2|2013\n|[[City People Entertainment Awards]]\n|Best Director\n|''[[Torn (2013 Nigerian film)|Torn]]''\n|{{won}}<ref>https://tooxclusive.com/2013-city-people-entertainment-awards-list-of-winners/</ref>\n|-\n|[[2013 Golden Icons Academy Movie Awards]]\n|1). Best Motion Picture, 2). Best Drama, 3). Best Supporting Actress, 4). Best Supporting Actor, 5). Best Director, 6). Producer of the Year\n|''[[Torn (2013 Nigerian film)|Torn]]''\n|{{nominated}}\n|-\n|rowspan=2|2014\n|[[2014 Nollywood Movies Awards]]\n|Best Director\n|''[[Torn (2013 Nigerian film)|Torn]]''\n|{{nominated}}\n|-\n|[[2014 Nollywood Movies Awards]]\n|Best Director\n|''[[Itoro (2013 Nigerian film)|Itoro]]''\n|{{nominated}}\n|-\n|rowspan=5|2015\n|[[Africa Movie Academy Awards]]\n|Best Comedy\n|''[[Last 3 Digits (2015 Nigerian film)|Last 3 Digits]]''\n|{{nominated}}\n|-\n|Nollywood Week, Paris, France\n|'''Official Selection'''\n|''[[Last 3 Digits (2015 Nigerian film)|Last 3 Digits]]''\n|\n|-\n|[[2015 Golden Icons Academy Movie Awards]]\n|1). Best Motion Picture, 2). Best Film, 3). Best Actor, 4). Best Actress, 5). Best Supporting Male, 6). Best Supporting Female, 7). Best New Actress, 8). Best on Screen Duo, 9). Best Screenplay, 10). Best Director \n|''[[Stalker (2016 film)|Stalker]]''\n|{{nominated}}\n|-\n|[[2015 Golden Icons Academy Movie Awards]]\n|1). Best Actor, 2). Best Actress, 3). Best Film\n|''[[Stalker (2016 film)|Stalker]]''\n|{{